author: NSPBWii
text:
I guess it's time for another checkpoint. This will definitely get lost in between all the checkpoints, but i don't care. It's been around 4 months since my last checkpoint in the Stickerbrush Symphony video. So much has changed since then. I started to act upon my dreams, i guess. I'm still taking baby steps, but it's better than nothing.

The pizza parlor i used to work for closed due to lack of rent payment. My father and i have almost no money. We keep getting enough to survive long enough. He asks loans to people he knows, and he pays them with money from a job that pays 9000 pesos in 3 month intervals, and also some surprise money he gets from many different errands. The car broke out a month ago, so until we get money for repairs, we won't have a car. That takes a degree of freedom. Not having a job takes another. Not having adecuate equipment to do excercises removes yet another. The current crisis takes yet another one.

I don't feel free at all, but at least i'm surviving long enough. And as i said, i started to take action in my dreams. Recently, i gave a conference for the first time. I'm working on my first videogame, making it better until i have some money to pay for the copyright and a website to host my works. I'm also doing a blog, writing my truth. Yesterday i streamed my favorite games in Facebook Live, and the reception from the few spectators i had was overall positive. I'm planing to turn my blog posts into videos, to reach more people that might need to hear what i have to say.

But change is tough. I still doubt myself from time to time. I'm full of fear. I'm afraid that my situation will never get better, no mather how hard i try. I'm afraid that on 10 years from now i'll still be poor, struggling to survive. Doing exactly what my dad does.

As of the "Nice Guy" i've been, I am working on not being that anymore. I've been pushing the boundaries, asserting myself and what i believe in. That naturally moved away some people. I feel lonely. I feel like nobody understands me, and what i want. Everything i believed true is starting to show up as a lie. I might not be important for nobody, after all. I'm not my best friends' best friend. I might be just another friend that they let stay there because it's convenient.

I can't talk about any of this, about my feelings, with anybody. The girls i date stop being attracted to me when i try to open up. They start treating me like a friend. Some of my friends are sick of my bullshit because it appears that i only wallow in my misery, and i'm not interested on moving forward. But i'm just trying to understand my problem, so i can solve it. I don't talk about this with my family because i don't think they would understand. And that leaves me with myself. The only person i can really trust. But how can i lift myself if i'm the one who needs to be lifted?

I found the girl i talked about, on Tinder, a few months ago. We matched. She had a boyfriend, but they broke up quite quickly. We started talking again. I thought i had another chance to make things right, to do what i couldn't before. We matured. We were better people. We could take another chance, right?

Wrong. She only cared about my attention. I Quickly made the same mistakes, but now i was the one who broke up with her, because i could not stand how one-sided our relationship was, how little she cared for me, how much did she judge me. I blocked her. Deep down, i was expecting her to learn, to come back, so we could finally be better for each other. She was so pretty, we had so much chemistry. If only she could be more caring we would've had something great. But she didn't. I could not change her. She didn't care at all. She never came back.

Nothing feels real anymore. What's the point of dating? It's not like i don't have someone to date. There are plenty of people that want to date me. That's what i wanted 6 years before. But now it doesn't feel good. I feel broken. I also feel insecure, maybe even more than before i started to date people. But even if i was confident in myself, I don't see the point anymore. I didn't wanted to feel lonely. I wanted someone who could care for me. But nobody cares. Maybe only my family, and they will die some day. What will i do then? How can i be successful if i can't even endure being lonely?

Maybe i'll figure out something. I'm at least starting. Starting now is better than never starting. I needed this checkpoint to show up, so i could reflect on how far i've come, and what does still hurt. I like writing in here because nobody will read it anyway. At least no one i know. I can be myself. I'm tired of giving and not being appreciated. I want to relax for a bit, take a breath. But there's no pause button for life. I gotta keep going if i want to have a life where i don't just survive. I want to cry. I thought i've came far, but i haven't. But at least i'm doing something towards my dreams. I don't want loneliness to have a grip on my life anymore. I want to accept that only i care about myself.

See you in the next checkpoint, where i'll (hopefully) figure this out. Thanks for reading, and keep going forward.

17/08/2020
A 23 Years Old Man from Mexico.

Welp, here I am. This is actually my 10th checkpoint.
I didnt post anything on the others since i wanted to hit up the Chrono Trigger ones first, but I guess i'll talk about my experience with the Donkey Kong franchise...



I've never played DKC2, but I played DKC3 Dixie's Double Trouble for the GBA.
It was my first game, which I got alongside my first console, a Silver GBA, all from my Cousin.

I got a far as the bosses of Cottontop Cove and the Factory World. I didn't understand all the mechanics me playing betwee. 6-8 years old, and never got past them.

My Parents had a breakup when i was around 8 and I was wisked to another state, and me not knowing why i was leaving, couldnt find my GBA (I later learned since my father was being unfaithful, the kids of the other person he had over had stolen my GBA and Charger.)

I never have played another game in the series simply by chance.

However, last year, a friend got me a copy of VBA, and some ROMs for a lot of the games i liked on it.
Among them was DKC3.

It took me for a while to touch the game, but i finally got to it in April of this year.

For those of you who saw my posts in the Chrono Trigger checkpoints know what happned.
I lost my Cousin who gave me my GBA, DKC3, and my Childhood to Covid-19, and I started playing the exact day he passed.

After all the little grieving and stress that happened, I dedicated my time to finishing the game in his honor. And that's exactly what I did: 100% cleared the game alongside Krematoa in a single sitting, in 14 hours.

...And that's my story for Donkey Kong. I'll share this at the checkpoints.
It's 2:22 am EST at the time of writing... and I can only wish you guys the best.
Please stay safe in these hard times... others shouldn't have to suffer the loss of you, especially if your younger. My cousin was in his early 20's when he passed this April... so it can affect younger peeps too.

author: Nido Ravensbeard
text:
Checkpoint:

After a somewhat calm summer, I got back in touch with my childhood best friend... who was about to be kicked out of his home.
okay, to be fair it technically wasn't his home, it was his friend's home he'd been staying at because he had been ALREADY kicked out of his home. He used to live with his grandmother and sister when I last saw him, having a mother who abandoned him when he was a little kid and a father who's a deadbeat drinker. He apparently had been fighting with his grandmother and it got so bad that she kicked him out. He moved in with his great-grandma Jo who sadly passed away, and then finally moved in with his buddy. He got a job at the ranch, but since he constantly missed time due to him not having any mode of transportation to get there, he got fired which resulted in the parents of his buddy kicking him out. He was still legally a minor when he came to our house, and begged my mom to let him stay the night so he could get a job interview at KFC the next day. He had tried to get into the Marines a few months ago, he had wanted to join the Army but the marine guy was trying to sweet-talk him into joining the marine instead. They declined him a few weeks later due to him having anxiety and clinical depression, so he just gave up on that. I remember that day, he told us he'd be 19 in 6 days (in Nebraska, the legal age of adulthood is 19) and we sat down (my mom, her boyfriend, my friend and I) and told him he should join the Army like he had hoped to do.

we told him "tomorrow, you go to the job interview, you go to the recruiters, and you call authorities when it comes to finding a place to stay because you are still technically a minor." and he did all of them- well... he went to his shitty stepmother and asked if he could stay with her, which she said yes. my mom had been debating whether or not to just let him stay with us until he needed to go to the army, which ended up happening in the end because... the stepmom told him that he'd have to give her ALL his money, AND we found out he was having to sleep in a tent outside the house because she had "no space". we were pissed, we took him in, when I saw the tent I got so pissed and didn't even look at the face of that woman. It smelled inside, like as if she hadn't really been letting him wash himself or his clothes.

He's staying with us for a little over a week, every day at 5:00 PM we train. on the off days we do yoga, and the other days we train military style. He goes to the recruiters every day, and we try our best to make every day a good one. My friend and I are complete opposites, but he's like an older brother to me. He's had the shittiest life from day 1, and yet he's still trying every day to do the best he can. I can not express how proud of him I am. He's been there for me my whole childhood, keeping me calm and out playing while I was being abused from my ex-stepdad, so if there's anything I can do for him, I will.


If you feel like there's nothing to do, if you feel like your life is being unfair, just know you are worth it. though I don't know who you are, I believe you CAN do this. Fight on, and smile :)

text:
Dāvis Šteinbergs ummm.... checkpoint...

So it’s been about a month since he was staying with us. After a while he didn’t seem like he was trying with anything, he would constantly eat which... really put a big dent in my mom’s wallet, and the first few days he started calling my mom HIS mom, which didn’t make her feel that very comfortable... but we still tried our best to help him.

I should have noticed it way sooner, the red flags were there. Whenever we would want to work out or run, he would give little to no effort. Whenever we were like “okay, we’re going to run 2 miles! Just go at your own pace” he would just be like “oh, I don’t think I can do two miles” so we were like “they’re going to push you HARD in the military, come on!” So he barely agreed but it seemed like he was doing it just to make us happy. He didn’t try hard at all.

He had his job at KFC... all for a week before being fired. He told us that he got fired because he told some coworkers that he was going to the army. Coworkers he doesn’t know all that well.

We told him that he needed to go to the recruiters every day, and my mom even offered to give him a ride since it was further than his job, and she always gave him a ride THERE. But he refused and just wanted to walk.

A few weeks ago we were thinking that this whole process was taking FOREVER, and so when we asked him about it he was like “oh they just need my medical stuff” so when he got that stuff he walked to the recruter. He told us everything was rolling.

We visited my great grandma and my grandpa, who said that he’d gladly give him a job at his work, so he gaver him an interview, and a book he’d need to read. He doesn’t have a drivers license, and he’d be working with cargo and trucks... but my grandpa was still okay with getting him this job.

About a week ago my mom had a list of things for us to do, chores she wanted us to have around the house so it’d look nice. The first day was fine, though for some reason my friend wasn’t reading the pamphlet for the rules about working on the trucks, nor was he getting his bike fixed.

3 days ago, he didn’t even bother with any of the chores, while I was working outside. He mainly was just sitting watching TV, and my mom told me that she had asked him why he wasn’t working and he said “well I just don’t want Odin to have nothing to do on that list.” And soooo yeah. Later that night he said he was going to go to his buddies place in the morning so he’d be able to fix his bike. (He had been saying that for this for weeks)

Now yesterday he went to his friends, but didn’t take his bike... so my mom decided “it’s probably a good idea to call the recruiter myself” and so she did...

They said “we do not have a (my friend’s full name) in the record.” We tried to figure out if it was a glitch or a misunderstanding but in the end... he had lied about being able to go into the army. When he went to the marines, they said he wasn’t mentally fit to be in the marines. But the lie came in the fact that if you are not mentally fit to be in the marines, you can not be mentally fit to join ANY branch... for weeks and weeks he had been lying to us and basically squatting...

He spent the night at his friend’s house, we didn’t tell him we knew or anything... he’s still not here but when he gets here we’re gonna have to tell him that we know, and that he needs to go back with his grandmother’s. The fact that he would lie to everyone, to ME after everything we were doing for him, and for SO LONG... it’s just... it fucking sucks.

It goes to prove that, again... no one is a perfect human being. No one. We try our best for the very reason we want to be better, but we will never be perfect. And you know what, that’s completely fine! Perfect doesn’t really exist in general... but... you don’t do that... this was a great learning experience for me, and it will be the biggest learning experience when he walks through that front door.

author: Joseph B.
text:
Fellipe Dasilva - You’re missing the point. The music itself is merely a nice accompaniment; it holds no spiritual symbolism or practical significance. I can’t speak for everyone in this comment section, but I’m pretty sure that the reason they’re all here isn’t because they have superstitious opinions about nostalgic DKC music. If they do, I think they are well-intentioned, but sadly misguided. 

This comment section serves as a convenient gathering place for people to open up and honestly express their emotions and opinions on life. This is a rare opportunity on the Internet today, with so many malicious political freaks, cruel trolls, and fakes who want to censor, harass, and steal the spotlight from common people. This old video evokes a simpler time, before the world started getting crazy. In a practical sense, it’s very far away from the chaotic social media sites that have severed human connection or even ruined people’s lives in favor of momentary popularity and dishonest pleasure. It’s a statistical fact that social media causes depression, but this comment section is different. On this derelict video, the commenters have given up the usual competition for likes and began connecting with each other on a truly incredible level. There’s no need to worry about who has the top comment or who has the wittiest joke. There is a renewed sense of individualism among these commenters which I have hardly seen anywhere else on the Internet. It’s all about human connection, which is what social media has failed to provide. 

In a nutshell, this video is special, because it’s a haven from the chaos and fakeness of social media, allowing people to truly share their life experiences and connect with each other; the music is just some nice background noise.

Rare takes the cartoony characters of DKC and puts them in a moody rich atmospheric setting with tons of lore, depth, charm and ambience which fits perfectly contrasted by the silly fun cartoon-like characters of DKC. I really love Retro Studio's Donkey Kong Country Returns series, but to me they don't have as much atmospheric ambience like the first three games which is what really made DKC's identity imo.
